- "subjects" are the specific courses or topics being tested;
- "instructors" are the teachers responsible for the exams;
- "attendance rank = 1" means the exam with the highest attendance count for each room.

- "Second semester" refers to the second term in an academic year;
- "Midterms" are examinations typically held in the middle of a semester;
- "Number of students" indicates the total count of students taking each exam.

- An "educator" refers to an instructor in the academic context;
- A "web of exam conflicts" metaphorically refers to the number of exam scheduling conflicts;
- "Weaving through the intricate tapestry of academic schedules" implies the complexity and interconnection of exam schedules;
- "Threads of conflict" metaphorically represents the number of conflicts.

- Time conflicts in exams refer to overlaps in exam times that may cause scheduling issues for students or staff;
- Resolved conflicts mean that the scheduling issues have been addressed and the exams can proceed as planned;
- Scheduled exams are those that are planned to occur in the future and are not yet completed;
- In-progress exams with zero attendance are considered cancelled or abandoned.

- `conflict_flag = 0` indicates that there is no scheduling conflict for the exam;
- `status = 'scheduled'` means the exam has been planned but not yet conducted;
- `s.semester = 'II'` refers to the second semester of the academic year.

sql:
